<html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/tips.css"></head><body><p><b>Use colors for data sources</b></p><p>You can use colors to distinguish between your data sources and their elements. To set a color to a data source or its object, right-click the element in the <span class="control">Database</span> tool window (<span class="shortcut">View | Tool Windows | Database</span>) and select <span class="control">Tools | Set Color</span>.</p><p class="image"><img src="images/tips_db_set_colors_for_objects.png" alt="Set data source colors" style="border: 1px solid #55555;" /></p></body></html>